    <!-- How Section -->
    <section class="container methods" data-aos="fade-up">
        <h1 class="title">HOW</h1>
        <p class="sub_title">To Start with Fish Farming Journey</p>
        <div class="method_box">
            <div class="method_">
                <div class="method_info" data-aos="fade-left">
                    <h3 class="method_title">Planning and Preparation</h3>
                    <p class="method_title_info">The first step in starting a fish farm is to plan and prepare for the
                        operation. This involves identifying the type of fish you want to farm, determining the size of
                        your farm, selecting an appropriate location, and obtaining any necessary permits or licenses.
                        You will also need to decide on a suitable farming system, such as a pond or a recirculating
                        aquaculture system (RAS), and set up the necessary infrastructure, such as tanks, filters, and
                        aeration systems.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="method_img" data-aos="fade-right">
                    <img src="Gallery/pngwing.com (1).png" alt="Planning">
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="method_">
                <div class="method_img" data-aos="fade-left">
                    <img src="Gallery/pngwing.com (2).png" alt="Planning">
                </div>
                <div class="method_info" data-aos="fade-right">
                    <h3 class="method_title">Stocking and Cultivation</h3>
                    <p class="method_title_info">Once your farm is set up, the next step is to stock it with fish and
                        begin the cultivation process. This involves selecting healthy and disease-free fish fry or
                        fingerlings, and monitoring their growth and development over time. You will need to provide the
                        fish with a suitable diet, maintain appropriate water quality and temperature, and manage any
                        disease or pest outbreaks that may occur.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="method_">
                <div class="method_info" data-aos="fade-left">
                    <h3 class="method_title">Harvesting and Marketing</h3>
                    <p class="method_title_info">The final step in fish farming is to harvest your fish and bring them
                        to market. Depending on the type of fish you are farming, this may involve harvesting the fish
                        live or processing them for sale as fillets or other products. You will also need to develop a
                        marketing strategy and network to sell your fish to buyers, such as restaurants, markets, or
                        wholesalers.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="method_img" data-aos="fade-right">
                    <img src="Gallery/pngwing.com (3).png" alt="Planning">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
