    <!-- Why Section -->
    <section class="why container" data-aos="fade-up">
        <h1 class="title">WHY</h1>
        <p class="sub_title">Fish Farming ?</p>
        <div class="why_container">
            <div class="why_info" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="600">
                <div class="why_info_logo">
                    <i class="uil uil-shop info_icon"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="why_description">
                    The global seafood market was valued at USD 158.2 billion in 2020 and is projected to reach USD
                    195.9 billion by 2026, growing at a CAGR of 3.6% during the forecast period (2021-26). The market is
                    driven by the increasing demand of seafood products.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="why_info" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="900">
                <div class="why_info_logo">
                    <i class="uil uil-arrow-growth info_icon"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="why_description">
                    Fish farming can have lower production costs compared to traditional agriculture, as fish require
                    less feed and water than other livestock. This can result in higher profit margins for farrmers.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="why_info" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="400">
                <div class="why_info_logo">
                    <i class="uil uil-shopping-cart-alt info_icon"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="why_description">
                    Fish farming create opportunities for local markets, as fish can be sold to nearby restaurants
                    and grocery stores. It also provide export opportunities for countries with competitive advantage in
                    fish production.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="why_info" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="600">
                <div class="why_info_logo">
                    <i class="uil uil-usd-circle info_icon"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="why_description">
                    Fish farming provide steady source of income for fish farmers, as fish can be sold year-round. This
                    can help to stabilize the income of farmers, especially where agriculture is seasonal.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="why_info" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="900">
                <div class="why_info_logo">
                    <i class="uil uil-server info_icon"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="why_description">
                    Fish farming is an efficient use of resources, as it requires less water than traditional
                    agriculture and can be located in areas where land is not suitable for other types of agriculture.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="why_info" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="400">
                <div class="why_info_logo">
                    <i class="uil uil-users-alt info_icon"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="why_description">
                    Fish farming provides employment opportunities for people in rural areas, where other employment
                    opportunities may be limited.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
